Date: Thu, 21 Nov 2019 13:59:44 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 019/322] [FIO extras] qemu: set CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN to 32M

Allow kernel size up to 32M.

Signed-off-by: Ricardo Salveti <ricardo@foundries.io>
---
 include/configs/qemu-arm.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/include/configs/qemu-arm.h b/include/configs/qemu-arm.h
index 273fa1a7d7b..c85c72baddb 100644
--- a/include/configs/qemu-arm.h
+++ b/include/configs/qemu-arm.h
@@ -11,6 +11,7 @@
 /* Physical memory map */
 
 #define CONFIG_SYS_SDRAM_BASE		0x40000000
+#define CONFIG_SYS_BOOTM_LEN		SZ_32M
 
 /* The DTB generated by QEMU is placed at start of RAM, stay away from there */
 #define CONFIG_SYS_INIT_SP_ADDR         (CONFIG_SYS_SDRAM_BASE + SZ_2M)
